title: Zelenskyy blocked from making address at Eurovision - as final qualifiers announced
description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy has been blocked from making an address at the Eurovision Song Contest ahead of the final this weekend.

title: One dead and five wounded in Israel as Gaza launches more than 600 rockets in 48 hours
description: One Israeli has been killed and five wounded in a missile strike launched from Gaza on the central Israeli town of Rehovot on Thursday evening.

title: South Africa accused of providing arms to Russia - US ambassador
description: The US ambassador to South Africa has accused the country of providing weapons and ammunition to Russia for its war in Ukraine via a cargo ship that docked secretly at a naval base near Cape Town for three days in December.

title: A billion pounds' worth of unsold Yeezy trainers to find new homes
description: Adidas has said it plans to sell some of its Yeezy trainers and merchandise from its defunct partnership with Kanye West and donate some of the proceeds to charity.

title: Biden says he visited Ireland to 'make sure the Brits didn't screw around'
description: Joe Biden says he visited the island of Ireland last month to make sure the "Brits didn't screw around".

title: Pakistan's supreme court says Imran Khan's arrest was illegal and orders his release
description: Pakistan's supreme court has said the arrest of former prime minister Imran Khan was illegal and ordered his release from custody.

title: Ten firefighters and two police officers injured after resident 'triggers blast' at apartment block in Germany
description: Ten firefighters and two police officers have been injured after a resident used an unidentified object to cause a blast at an apartment block in Germany, a state interior minister in the country has said.

title: What to expect when US border law Title 42 ends
description: Title 42 is a law that enables the US to halt entries into the country to stop the introduction of communicable diseases.

title: Explosion in centre of Milan leaves several vehicles on fire
description: Vehicles are on fire in the centre of Milan after an explosion, according to reports.

title: Convicted killer faces extradition over unsolved disappearance of teenager
description: Peru will allow the extradition to the US of the main suspect in the unsolved disappearance of student Natalee Holloway on the Dutch Caribbean island of Aruba in 2005.

title: Russia threatens 'military response' after UK gives long-range missiles to Ukraine
description: The UK has been threated with a "military response" by Russia after pledging to send long-range missiles to Ukraine.

title: UK sending Storm Shadow long-range missiles to Ukraine, defence secretary confirms
description: The UK is sending long-range missiles to Ukraine, Defence Secretary Ben Wallace has confirmed.

title: One dead and another severely injured after shooting at Mercedes Benz plant in Germany
description: One person has died and another has been severely injured after a shooting at a Mercedes Benz plant in Germany, police have said.

title: Fourth Palestinian Islamic Jihad commander dies as Israeli airstrikes kill 20
description: A fourth Palestinian Islamic Jihad commander has been killed in Israeli airstrikes on the Gaza Strip which have left young children among the dead.
